# sources/wget-list-sysv — REFERENCE ONLY (the SysVinit path we did NOT take)
# =============================================================================
# ft_linux is built as the *systemd* variant of LFS (a choice the spec
# explicitly permits: mandatory.md offers "SysV OR SystemD", and packages.md
# says the example packages — incl. udev — may be swapped for equivalents).
#
# This file exists purely for AUDITABILITY of that deviation: it records the
# packages that the SysVinit path would have used and that the systemd path
# therefore OMITS. The effective, authoritative list is sources/wget-list
# (derived from env/versions.sh). The full rationale + role-mapping table lives
# in docs/03-systemd-deviation.md and docs/06-package-manifest.md.
#
# This is intentionally NOT a complete divergent URL list — the ~64 shared
# packages are identical to wget-list. Only the init/udev/logging trio differs.
#
# SysVinit-path packages REPLACED in the systemd build:
#
#   spec #14  Eudev              -> systemd-udevd        (kernel-module loader)
#   spec #63  Udev-lfs Tarball   -> (provided by systemd, no separate tarball)
#   spec #58  Sysvinit           -> systemd (PID 1)      (central management)
#   spec #57  Sysklogd           -> systemd-journald     (system logging)
#
# Representative SysVinit-path URLs (for the record; NOT downloaded by this
# build — verify exact versions against the SysVinit LFS book if ever used):
#
#   https://github.com/eudev-project/eudev/releases/download/v3.2.14/eudev-3.2.14.tar.gz
#   https://anduin.linuxfromscratch.org/LFS/udev-lfs-20230818.tar.xz
#   https://github.com/slicer69/sysvinit/.../sysvinit-3.xx.tar.xz
#   https://www.infodrom.org/projects/sysklogd/download/sysklogd-2.x.x.tar.gz
#   (+ the LFS bootscripts tarball, used only on the SysVinit path)
#
# Everything else (the ~64 other packages) is the SAME as sources/wget-list.
# =============================================================================
